UNIVERSAL EPISTEMIC ARCHITECTURE — MASTER
================================================================================
Domain-agnostic pipeline for reconstructing hidden structure from noisy traces:

Reality R → Traces T (𝒯) → Observations S (𝒪) → Evidence E (𝓘) → Model H → Narrative/Theory N (π)

Differences across fields are confined to:
• Trace types and regime characteristics (Q_T)
• Domain-specific semantics of operators
• Interpretation of components in H (e.g. "actors" vs "particles", "events" vs "states")

PART I — CLASSICAL HISTORICAL METHOD
[0] PURPOSE: Reconstruct R from surviving evidence via criticism & synthesis.
[1] FORMULATE QUESTION → Define target + scope + evidence criteria
[2] SOURCE ACQUISITION (broad → filter) → Primary + Secondary
[3] SOURCE CRITICISM: External (Authenticity) → Internal (Credibility) → R_vec = (A,C,B,Tq,P)
[4] CONTEXTUALIZATION → Embed in period norms (avoid anachronism)
[5] INTERPRETATION (𝓘) → Causal chains, competing explanations, fact/inference split
[6] SYNTHESIS → Coherent H from validated E; resolve or flag contradictions
[7] REVIEW & REVISION → ℋ iteration on new evidence

PART II — FORMAL MODEL
H = (G_S, G_C, V, Ctx, W, U, M)
• G_S : State/Event graph
• G_C : Causal/Interaction graph
• V   : Variable/Actor states (incl. latents Z)
• Ctx : Contextual/Environmental fields
• W   : Evidence weights & alignment (R_i, M(t))
• U   : Uncertainty + consistency (posteriors, τ)
• M   : Methodological state (priors, ℛ, f, λ)

Trace = Record residue.  
Observation = Measurement/recording of trace.  
Interpretation = Assignment of meaning + criticism.  
Evidence = Interpreted, weighted, relevant observations.  
Model H = Coherent internal reconstruction.  
N = Communicated projection of H.

PART III — ADVANCED COMPUTATIONAL LAYERS
• Multi-Level Bayesian Hierarchies
• Message-Passing Inference on SDG/DAG
• Sheaf Consistency + TDA (τ = persistence(β₁))
• Meta-Learning Loop
• Bayesian Experimental Design (EVI)
• Multi-Objective Pareto Optimization (𝓝*)
• Decision Layer + Scalability (Budget B, clustering)

RDG INTEGRATION
This pipeline is a direct instantiation of the SID-PED-Q engine:
- SID: Structure (graphs in H), Interaction (operators), Dynamics (ℋ, long-memory)
- PED: Power (operator capacity), Evaluation (reliability f, τ, loss), Dynamics_slice (Q regimes)
- Q: Regime logic gating traces → meta-updates

Viewed as a Closure Engine operating on epistemic flux: closing loops between observed traces and inferred model states.

FORMAL OVERLAY (Active Throughout)
• Operators: 𝒯 : R→T ; 𝒪 : T→S ; 𝓘 : S→E ; Composite with Var(E) propagation
• Reliability: R_i = f(R_vec_i) [meta-learned]
• Models: Latent Z, M(t) decay, long-memory P(H_t | H_<t)
• Inference: SDG/DAG message-passing, Bayesian update, Pareto 𝓝*
• Consistency: Sheaf gluing + TDA τ
• Loop: EVI(S*) + ℋ(H_t, E_t) → (H_{t+1}, Q_{t+1})
• Meta: (M₀, ℛ) updated via prediction loss ∇
• Scalability: B + cluster_𝓝 + d_GH
• Decision: Posterior P(N_i) → δ via U(·)
